h323TerminalMIB.name: h323TerminalMIB

revisions.description: The initial version of the H323 terminal mib

h323TerminalMIB.contactinfo: Joon Maeng VTEL Corp. Postal: 108 Wild Basin Rd. Austin, TX 78746 USA TEL: (512)437-4567 Email: Joon_Maeng@vtel.com
h323TerminalMIB.description: This MIB module supports the functions of an ITU H.323 terminal

h323TerminalUptime.name: h323TerminalUptime
h323TerminalUptime.description: The amount of time (in hundredths of a second) since this H323 terminal was last initialized. Note that this is different from sysUpTime in MIB-II [ ] because sysUpTime is the uptime of the network management portion of the system.

h323TerminalLocalTime.name: h323TerminalLocalTime
h323TerminalLocalTime.description: The local date and time of day.

h323TerminalDiagnostics.name: h323TerminalDiagnostics
h323TerminalDiagnostics.description: Indicates the results of the last diagnostic routine performed noResults(1) No diagnostic has yet been performed, passed(2) the diagnostic has been passed, hardwareFault(3) Hardware fault was detected, softwareFault(4) Software fault was detected

h323TerminalMaxLineRate.name: h323TerminalMaxLineRate
h323TerminalMaxLineRate.description: This object represents maximum line rate of combined audio/video and data of this terminal.

h323TerminalVideoCaps.name: h323TerminalVideoCaps
h323TerminalVideoCaps.description: This object represents the video capabilities of this terminal. This includes the various video algorithms that it supports. It is encoded as bits in an octet string, with the following definitions: Capability Bit # h261CIFVideo 0 h261QCIFVideo 1 h263SQCIFVideo 2 h263QCIFVideo 3 h263CIFVideo 4 h263CIF4Video 5 h263CIF16Video 6 h262SPMLSIFVideo 7 h262SPML2SIFVideo 8 h262SPML4SIFVideo 9 h262MPMLSIFVideo 10 h262MPML2SIFVideo 11 h262MPML4SIFVideo 12 Bits are numbered starting with the most significant bit of the first byte being bit 0, the least significant bit of the first byte being bit 7, the most significant bit of the second byte being bit 8, and so on. A one bit encodes that the capability is supported, a zero bit encodes that the capability is not supported.

h323TerminalMaxVideoRate.name: h323TerminalMaxVideoRate
h323TerminalMaxVideoRate.description: The maximum bit rate that the video channel can do.

h323TerminalAudioCaps.name: h323TerminalAudioCaps
h323TerminalAudioCaps.description: This object represents the audio capabilities of this terminal. This includes the various audio algorithms that it supports. It is encoded as bits in an octet string, with the following definitions: Capability Bit # g711-ALaw64KAudio 0 g711-ALaw56KAudio 1 g711-ULaw64KAudio 2 g711-ULaw56KAudio 3 g722-64KAudio 4 g722-56KAudio 5 g722-48KAudio 6 g728Audio 7 g723.1-5.3KAudio 8 g723.1-6.4KAudio 9 g729Audio 10 Bits are numbered starting with the most significant bit of the first byte being bit 0, the least significant bit of the first byte being bit 7, the most significant bit of the second byte being bit 8, and so on. A one bit encodes that the capability is supported, a zero bit encodes that the capability is not supported.

h323TerminalDataCaps.name: h323TerminalDataCaps
h323TerminalDataCaps.description: This object represents the data application capability of the terminal. It is encoded as bits in an octet string, with the following definitions: Capability Bit # t.120 0 dsm-cc 1 userData 2 t84 3 t434 4 h224 5 nlpid 6 dsvdControl 7 h222DataPartitioning 8 t30fax 9 t140 10 Others 11 Bits are numbered starting with the most significant bit of the first byte being bit 0, the least significant bit of the first byte being bit 7, the most significant bit of the second byte being bit 8, and so on. A one bit encodes that the capability is supported, a zero bit encodes that the capability is not supported.

h323TerminalEncrypCaps.name: h323TerminalEncrypCaps
h323TerminalEncrypCaps.description: This object represents the encryption capability of the terminal. Capability Bit # H.235 0 Others 1 Bits are numbered starting with the most significant bit of the first byte being bit 0, the least significant bit of the first byte being bit 7, the most significant bit of the second byte being bit 8, and so on. A one bit encodes that the capability is supported, a zero bit encodes that the capability is not supported.

h323TerminalRDCCaps.name: h323TerminalRDCCaps
h323TerminalRDCCaps.description: This object represents the Remote Device Control capability of the terminal. FECC 0 -- Far-end Camera Control Others 1 Bits are numbered starting with the most significant bit of the first byte being bit 0, the least significant bit of the first byte being bit 7, the most significant bit of the second byte being bit 8, and so on. A one bit encodes that the capability is supported, a zero bit encodes that the capability is not supported.

h323TerminalSiteName.name: h323TerminalSiteName
h323TerminalSiteName.description: Name of the site where the H323 terminal is located.

h323TerminalfType.name: h323TerminalfType
h323TerminalfType.description: The interface type on which this site can be called. The interface type identified by this value is the same type of as the ifType from Interface Table in RFC1213.

h323TerminalIPAddress.name: h323TerminalIPAddress
h323TerminalIPAddress.description: The IP address of the terminal.

h323TerminalAdminControl.name: h323TerminalAdminControl
h323TerminalAdminControl.description: The desired state of the H323 terminal. Setting the value if this object to these values will have the following actions: run(1) The H323 terminal will enter the run state, reset(2) The H323 terminal will reset, diagnose(3) Will activate the diagnostic routine stop(4) Will halt the H323 terminal.

h323TerminalCallSetUp.name: h323TerminalCallSetUp
h323TerminalCallSetUp.description: establish a call to another video conference terminal. Set this value to the index of the site of the video conference site you want to dial in the Site Table and the system will be dialed.

h323TerminalCallHangup.name: h323TerminalCallHangup
h323TerminalCallHangup.description: Hang up the video conference call in progess now.

h323EnableLocalLoopback.name: h323EnableLocalLoopback
h323EnableLocalLoopback.description: Enable or disable local loop back on a video conference system. Local loopbacks loop back the audio, video and data streams in a call. Once looped back, a new call will show up in the Call Table and the user can observe the audio/video/data rates to assure that these components are working properly.

h323EnableRemoteLoopback.name: h323EnableRemoteLoopback
h323EnableRemoteLoopback.description: Enable or disable remote loop back on a video conference system. Remote loopbacks loop back the audio and video streams from the remote system in a call.. When the remote system calls in, a new call will show up in the Call Table and the user can observe the audio/video/data rates to assure that these components are coming in properly from the remote system.

h323TerminalDesrGroup.name: h323TerminalDesrGroup
h323TerminalDesrGroup.description: A collection of objects providing the description of the terminal

h323TerminalCapsGroup.name: h323TerminalCapsGroup
h323TerminalCapsGroup.description: A collection of objects providing capabilities of the terminal

h323TerminalConfigGroup.name: h323TerminalConfigGroup
h323TerminalConfigGroup.description: A collection of objects providing the ability to configure the terminal

h323TerminalControlGroup.name: h323TerminalControlGroup
h323TerminalControlGroup.description: A collection of objects providing the ability to invoke terminal functions

h323TerminalCompliance.name: h323TerminalCompliance
h323TerminalCompliance.description: The set of objects required for compliance
